You can use the desired JDK with a [docker agent][1].
With this, you can defined an image which use the appropriate JDK or any image.

For example, in your case, you can have the JDK 11 for jenkins itself and the one you want in each job. Example with openjdk : 

    pipeline {
        agent {
            docker { image &#39;openjdk:11&#39; }
        }
        stages {
            stage(&#39;Test java version&#39;) {
                steps {
                    sh &#39;java -version&#39;
                }
            }
        }
    }

You can choose the [tag][2] you want to select the appropriate version.

You just need to setup docker in your jenkins instance.


  [1]: https://www.jenkins.io/doc/book/pipeline/docker/
  [2]: https://hub.docker.com/_/openjdk?tab=tags&amp;page=1&amp;ordering=last_updated

