The correct and safe method for close the resources associated with JDBC this (taken from [How to Close JDBC Resources Properly – Every Time][1]):

	Connection connection = dataSource.getConnection();
	try {
		Statement statement = connection.createStatement();

		try {
			ResultSet resultSet = statement.executeQuery(&quot;some query&quot;);

			try {
				// Do stuff with the result set.
			} finally {
				resultSet.close();
			}
		} finally {
			statement.close();
		}
	} finally {
		connection.close();
	}


  [1]: http://blog.shinetech.com/2007/08/04/how-to-close-jdbc-resources-properly-every-time/

